# Audio Recording for Keyword Spotting

This project enables audio recording using the XIAO ESP32S3 SENSE for creating training data for keyword spotting models in Edge Impulse.

## Project Overview
- Records audio samples using the onboard PDM microphone
- Designed specifically for the XIAO ESP32S3 SENSE board
- Creates audio files suitable for Edge Impulse training
- Focused on keyword spotting (KWS) applications

## Hardware Requirements
- Seeed Studio XIAO ESP32S3 SENSE
- USB cable for power and data transfer
- Computer for data collection

## Data Collection
The recorded audio samples can be:
- Used to train custom wake word models
- Uploaded directly to Edge Impulse
- Used for keyword spotting model development

## Usage
1. Connect your XIAO ESP32S3 SENSE to your computer
2. Upload this code to the board
3. Follow the serial monitor instructions to record samples
4. Collect both keyword and background noise samples

## Further Resources
- [Edge Impulse Documentation](https://docs.edgeimpulse.com)
- [XIAO ESP32S3 SENSE Wiki](https://wiki.seeedstudio.com/xiao_esp32s3_sense)

